My relationship with alcohol has always been rocky. More times then not, I didn‚Äôt like who I became when I started to feel buzzed. During quarantine, my relationship with alcohol became a nightly meeting. I would prioritize having a drink over doing some thing that actually made me feel good, that actually helped me to align with my highest self - tap into my sacred space. I was prioritizing the numbing buzz, over my own true self care. 

This last week threw some difficult and surprising curve balls at me. Mia a few months ago, would have polished off a box of wine by Friday night; numbing out, instead of tuned in. 

Over the last 2 months, I have leaned deeper into my self care rituals more than ever. My mind, body and soul feel the strongest and most connected they have ever felt. Every single day, I have carved out time to dedicate to myself- not to numb out.  I have moved, breathed, meditated, journaled and nourished myself, and in the process, I have created a beautiful sacred space. A space that lies with in me, that I can come back to when I have weeks full of curve balls. 

Prioritizing your self care is the most important gift you can give yourself. Letting go of habits that no longer serve you, is like finally setting down the weighted back pack you didn‚Äôt know you were carrying. 

‚ÄúEssential that we care for our unique body as a carrier of life magically forming within us as we make it through our days‚Äù - Mark Nepo 
